    "headerDoc": "STEP 886 — Orbit-Dynamical Unsolved Problems: Common Framework\n  ================================================================\n\n  Three unsolved problems share a common structure: iteration of a\n  number-theoretic map f : ℕ → ℕ with open termination/cycle question.\n\n    (1) Catalan-Dickson aliquot conjecture (1888/1913):\n        aliquot(n) = σ(n) - n. Does every orbit under `aliquot` hit\n        0 or a cycle? Open for n = 276, 552, 564, ...\n\n    (2) Sociable numbers:\n        k-cycles under `aliquot`. Perfect (k=1), amicable (k=2),\n        sociable (k ≥ 3) exist. Known 5-cycles, 28-cycles.\n "
